6968, "(fr)A good performance, Alpha. Your escort of the civilian transports and freighters - whilst under considerable pressure from Shivan attack wings - was done well, all things considered. The civilians you escorted, now safe and sound and well away from the Shivan presence, are no doubt thankful that you were there to help them in their hour of need.

Unfortunately, things have not gone so well elsewhere. As you already know, the GTVA blockade at the Tania Australis node fell apart earlier today, and the Nyarlathotep fleet gained complete access to both Tania Australis and the systems beyond.

Well, during your most recent sortie, Shivan forces attacked the Altaïr jump node. Thankfully, they bypassed Tau Sigma Station altogether, but we no longer have the resources to guard both the installation and the jump node. The Nyarlathotep now has three escape routes available to it - the Eridani cloud, the Australis outer colonies, and the very heart of GTVA space.

Things are looking grim, pilot. Be prepared to be called out at a moment's notice. If not... well, see you in six hours."

